tasks.description:
Add disk-backed caching to `RuntimeCache` so model data survives server restarts. The cache file lives at `${dorkHome}/cache/runtimes/claude-code/models.json` with a 24-hour TTL.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Update RuntimeCache constructor

In `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/runtime-cache.ts`, add a constructor that accepts `dorkHome` and `runtimeType`:

```typescript
import path from 'path';
import { readFileSync, writeFileSync, mkdirSync, existsSync } from 'fs';

interface ModelDiskCache {
  /** Cached model list from SDK */
  models: ModelOption[];
  /** ISO timestamp of when models were fetched */
  fetchedAt: string;
  /** SDK version that reported these models */
  sdkVersion: string;
  /** Cache format version for future migrations */
  version: 1;
}

export class RuntimeCache {
  private cachedModels: ModelOption[] | null = null;
  private warmupPromise: Promise<void> | null = null;
  private readonly cachePath: string;
  private readonly TTL_MS = 86_400_000; // 24 hours
  // ... existing fields (cachedSubagents, cachedMcpStatus, cachedSdkCommands)

  constructor(dorkHome: string, runtimeType: string = 'claude-code') {
    this.cachePath = path.join(dorkHome, 'cache', 'runtimes', runtimeType, 'models.json');
  }
```

### 2. Add loadFromDisk method

```typescript
/** Load models from disk cache if fresh. Returns true if loaded. */
private loadFromDisk(): boolean {
  try {
    if (!existsSync(this.cachePath)) return false;
    const raw = readFileSync(this.cachePath, 'utf-8');
    const parsed: ModelDiskCache = JSON.parse(raw);
    if (parsed.version !== 1 || !Array.isArray(parsed.models)) return false;
    if (this.isDiskCacheStale(parsed.fetchedAt)) return false;
    this.cachedModels = parsed.models;
    logger.debug('[RuntimeCache] loaded models from disk cache', {
      count: parsed.models.length,
      fetchedAt: parsed.fetchedAt,
    });
    return true;
  } catch (err) {
    logger.debug('[RuntimeCache] disk cache read failed', { err });
    return false;
  }
}
```

### 3. Add writeToDisk method

```typescript
/** Write current in-memory models to disk. */
private writeToDisk(): void {
  try {
    const dir = path.dirname(this.cachePath);
    if (!existsSync(dir)) mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });
    const cache: ModelDiskCache = {
      models: this.cachedModels ?? [],
      fetchedAt: new Date().toISOString(),
      sdkVersion: 'unknown', // populated when SDK provides version info
      version: 1,
    };
    writeFileSync(this.cachePath, JSON.stringify(cache, null, 2), 'utf-8');
    logger.debug('[RuntimeCache] wrote models to disk cache', { count: cache.models.length });
  } catch (err) {
    logger.warn('[RuntimeCache] disk cache write failed', { err });
  }
}
```

### 4. Add isDiskCacheStale method

```typescript
/** Check if disk cache is stale (> TTL or missing timestamp). */
private isDiskCacheStale(fetchedAt?: string): boolean {
  if (!fetchedAt) return true;
  return Date.now() - Date.parse(fetchedAt) > this.TTL_MS;
}
```

### 5. Update getSupportedModels to async with fallback chain

Change `getSupportedModels()` from sync to async. The `AgentRuntime` interface already declares it as `Promise<ModelOption[]>`, so this is compatible.

```typescript
/** Get models with lazy fallback: memory -> disk -> warm-up -> empty. */
async getSupportedModels(): Promise<ModelOption[]> {
  // 1. Memory cache (fastest)
  if (this.cachedModels) return this.cachedModels;

  // 2. Disk cache
  if (this.loadFromDisk()) return this.cachedModels!;

  // 3. Lazy warm-up with timeout
  if (this.defaultCwd) {
    try {
      await Promise.race([
        this.warmup(this.defaultCwd),
        new Promise((_, reject) =>
          setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('warmup timeout')), 3000)
        ),
      ]);
      if (this.cachedModels) return this.cachedModels;
    } catch {
      logger.debug('[RuntimeCache] lazy warm-up timed out or failed');
    }
  }

  // 4. Empty -- client shows loading state
  return [];
}
```

Note: `defaultCwd` will be set by the runtime (Task 2.3). For now, add a `private defaultCwd: string = ''` field and a setter method.

### 6. Remove DEFAULT_MODELS import

Remove the import of `DEFAULT_MODELS` from `runtime-constants.ts` at the top of `runtime-cache.ts`:

```typescript
// DELETE this line:
import { DEFAULT_MODELS } from './runtime-constants.js';
```

The fallback chain (memory -> disk -> warm-up -> empty) replaces the hardcoded defaults.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `RuntimeCache` constructor accepts `dorkHome: string` and `runtimeType: string` parameters
- [ ] `cachePath` is `${dorkHome}/cache/runtimes/${runtimeType}/models.json`
- [ ] `loadFromDisk()` reads valid cache, returns false for missing/corrupt/stale files
- [ ] `writeToDisk()` creates the directory structure if missing and writes valid JSON
- [ ] `isDiskCacheStale()` returns true when `fetchedAt` is older than 24 hours
- [ ] `getSupportedModels()` is async and follows the memory -> disk -> warm-up -> empty chain
- [ ] `DEFAULT_MODELS` import is removed from `runtime-cache.ts`
- [ ] TTL constant is 86,400,000ms (24 hours)

Implement the warm-up mechanism that creates a temporary SDK query to fetch the model list, and the mapper function that converts SDK `ModelInfo` objects to `ModelOption`. This task also updates `buildSendCallbacks` to always refresh models.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Create mapSdkModelToModelOption mapper

Add to `runtime-cache.ts` (or create a dedicated `model-mapper.ts` in the same directory -- `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/model-mapper.ts`):

```typescript
import type { ModelInfo } from '@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk';

/** Extract model family from a model ID (e.g., 'claude-opus-4' from 'claude-opus-4-6'). */
function extractFamily(modelId: string): string | undefined {
  // Match pattern: claude-{family}-{major}[-{minor}...]
  const match = modelId.match(/^(claude-\w+-\d+)/);
  return match?.[1];
}

/** Infer model tier from model ID for UI grouping. */
function inferTier(modelId: string): 'flagship' | 'balanced' | 'fast' | undefined {
  if (modelId.includes('opus')) return 'flagship';
  if (modelId.includes('sonnet')) return 'balanced';
  if (modelId.includes('haiku')) return 'fast';
  return undefined;
}

/** Map an SDK ModelInfo to the universal ModelOption schema. */
export function mapSdkModelToModelOption(m: ModelInfo): ModelOption {
  return {
    value: m.value,
    displayName: m.displayName,
    description: m.description,
    supportsEffort: m.supportsEffort,
    supportedEffortLevels: m.supportedEffortLevels,
    supportsAdaptiveThinking: m.supportsAdaptiveThinking,
    supportsFastMode: m.supportsFastMode,
    supportsAutoMode: m.supportsAutoMode,
    // Provider metadata (hardcoded for Claude Code runtime)
    provider: 'anthropic',
    family: extractFamily(m.value),
    tier: inferTier(m.value),
  };
}
```

Note: The SDK `ModelInfo` type may not include all these fields yet. Access them defensively: `m.supportsFastMode` will be `undefined` if the SDK hasn't added the field, which is fine since all `ModelOption` fields are optional.

### 2. Implement warmup method

Add to `RuntimeCache`:

```typescript
/**
 * Warm up the model cache. Creates a temporary SDK query
 * (never-yielding async iterable), fetches models, closes query.
 * Non-blocking -- returns a promise. Safe to call multiple times
 * (deduplicates via warmupPromise).
 */
async warmup(cwd: string): Promise<void> {
  // Deduplicate concurrent warm-up calls
  if (this.warmupPromise) return this.warmupPromise;

  this.warmupPromise = (async () => {
    try {
      // Create a query with a never-yielding async iterable
      const neverYield = async function* () { /* never yields */ };
      const agentQuery = query({ prompt: neverYield(), options: { cwd } });

      const models = await agentQuery.supportedModels();
      this.cachedModels = models.map(mapSdkModelToModelOption);
      this.writeToDisk();

      agentQuery.close();
      logger.debug('[RuntimeCache] warm-up complete', { count: this.cachedModels.length });
    } catch (err) {
      logger.warn('[RuntimeCache] warm-up failed', { err });
    } finally {
      this.warmupPromise = null;
    }
  })();

  return this.warmupPromise;
}
```

This requires importing `query` from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`. The import is allowed because this file lives within `services/runtimes/claude-code/` (the ESLint boundary).

### 3. Update buildSendCallbacks to always refresh models

In `runtime-cache.ts`, update `buildSendCallbacks` to always refresh models (remove the `!this.cachedModels ?` guard):

**Current:**
```typescript
onModelsReceived: !this.cachedModels
  ? (models) => {
      this.cachedModels = models;
      logger.debug('[sendMessage] cached supported models', { count: models.length });
    }
  : undefined,
```

**New:**
```typescript
onModelsReceived: (models) => {
  this.cachedModels = models.map(mapSdkModelToModelOption);
  this.writeToDisk();
  logger.debug('[sendMessage] refreshed model cache', { count: models.length });
},
```

Note: The `onModelsReceived` callback receives raw SDK model objects. The mapper normalizes them to `ModelOption`.

### 4. Update onModelsReceived type in MessageSenderOpts

In `message-sender.ts` (line ~54-62), the `onModelsReceived` callback has an inline type. Update it to accept the full SDK ModelInfo shape or use `ModelOption[]` import:

```typescript
onModelsReceived?: (
  models: Array<{
    value: string;
    displayName: string;
    description: string;
    supportsEffort?: boolean;
    supportedEffortLevels?: EffortLevel[];
    supportsAdaptiveThinking?: boolean;
    supportsFastMode?: boolean;
    supportsAutoMode?: boolean;
    [key: string]: unknown; // forward-compatible with future SDK fields
  }>
) => void;
```

Or simplify by importing `ModelInfo` from the SDK (allowed within this ESLint boundary).

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `mapSdkModelToModelOption` correctly maps all SDK fields to `ModelOption`
- [ ] `extractFamily('claude-opus-4-6')` returns `'claude-opus-4'`
- [ ] `inferTier` returns 'flagship' for opus, 'balanced' for sonnet, 'fast' for haiku
- [ ] `warmup()` creates a never-yielding query, calls `supportedModels()`, maps and caches the result, writes to disk, then closes the query
- [ ] `warmup()` deduplicates concurrent calls (only one SDK query at a time)
- [ ] `warmup()` clears `warmupPromise` in the `finally` block even on failure
- [ ] `buildSendCallbacks` always refreshes models (no first-call guard)
- [ ] `buildSendCallbacks` uses `mapSdkModelToModelOption` and calls `writeToDisk()`
- [ ] `onModelsReceived` type in `MessageSenderOpts` is updated for new SDK fields

